news.title: Gujarat: 2,429 cases of property attachment pending with district magistrates
news.para: According to the latest report by the State Level Bankers’ Committee (SLBC), 2,429 cases filed by banks seeking nod for attachment of properties are pending. This is costing the banks recovery to the tune of Rs 1,157 crore.

news.title: Government allows registration of Telangana Housing Board joint venture projects
news.para: The respite comes after GO No 1061, which was issued in May 2016, came into force recently after the Telangana Housing Board issued a letter dated May 7, 2022, to developers of over a dozen JV projects granting permission to proceed with registration formalities.

news.title: Telangana: High bid for Rajiv Swagruha plots, auction fetches Rs 15.3 crore
news.para: As many as 45 plots were sold and 190 bidders participated. The highest bid was Rs 19,000 per square yard and the lowest Rs 8,100 for one of the plots in the township.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property sale deeds under reassessment not online yet
news.para: The new system module, through which the documents can be uploaded online, was made available to the deputy collectors’ offices on June 8.

news.title: Registration department, Hyderabad civic body at odds over collection of property tax
news.para: GHMC has alleged that sub-registrar offices (SROs) were registering properties and executing transactions like sale deed, gift deed, mortgage deed, will deed and partition deed without collecting dues of property tax and vacant tax dues.

news.title: Venture X plans to invest $2-3 million by 2023 in co-working sector
news.para: Venture X has opened two co-working spaces in Gurugram with a cumulative 1,200 seats spread across 45,000 sq ft and 16,500 sq ft space at Sector 67 and 44 respectively.

news.title: Noida: Farmhouse owners submit objections to demolitions
news.para: Allahabad high court has ordered a status quo on the demolition drive and asked the owners to submit their objections. The Noida Authority will go through the objections before taking a call.

news.title: HDFC offloads 0.7% stake in Ansal Housing
news.para: "For recovery of part outstanding dues against loans availed by certain pledgers/borrowers, the Corporation on June 15, 2022, invoked the pledge on 50,00,000 shares of Ansal Housing (Ansal) aggregating 8.42 per cent of its paid-up share capital, pledged with the Corporation by the said pledger/borrower,"

news.title: Shuchi Patni of Wonder Cement buys Shanti Niketan property for Rs 84 crore
news.para: Experts said the scarcity of such properties available for outright sale near Lutyens’ zone, coupled with increasing demand for such bungalows, will ensure that prices remain high despite market fluctuations in other parts of Delhi.

news.title: Gurugram: Ansal Properties fined Rs 100 crore for violating environmental laws
news.para: ​The company will also have to pay additional environmental compensation to the Central Groundwater Authority for illegal extraction of groundwater without permission and a defunct rainwater harvesting system at Sushantlok Phase - 1, Gurugram.

news.title: China Evergrande sticks to restructuring plan target of before end-July
news.para: Reeling under more than $300 billion in liabilities, the firm's offshore debt is deemed to be in default after missing payment obligations late last year.

news.title: Mastercard inks 20-year lease for 4.23 lakh sq ft office space in Brookfield's Pune property
news.para: The deal is an indication of rising numbers of leasing through pre-commitments as corporates are locking in large office spaces across the country in the backdrop of reviving expansion plans. Large technology, consulting, and financial services firms like Google, Amazon, Qualcomm and Wells Fargo have pre-committed large office space across major cities in the last few quarters.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Nirmal Lifestyle Kalyan
news.para: Kolkata-based Srei Equipment Finance Ltd had approached the Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) after Nirmal Lifestyle Kalyan, an affiliate of Mumbai-based Nirmal Lifestyle Ltd, defaulted on its dues worth around Rs 84 crore.

news.title: Over 120 dangerous buildings in Ghaziabad, but no evacuation yet
news.para: ​Meanwhile, the list of those buildings has kept growing, with the GMC identifying 122 of them this year, including multi-storey towers and government buildings.

news.title: Seven arrested after builder's staff assault Noida society residents
news.para: The clash took place on Sunday at the Sunshine Helios premises in Sector 78, under Sector 113 police station limits, allegedly over conflict between the Apartment Owners Association (AoA) of the society and the builder's personal-hired security men, the officials said.
